replies.body:
Ah ok. I didn't see the tweet personally. 

Sounds to me like it was just a lashing out without any context as to why the boards is in a rough spot. Not a meaningful post about the reason riot doesnt stop by anymore. 

my bad {{sticker:sg-ahri-2}}

> [{quoted}](name=ßlended Fetus,realm=NA,application-id=6heBIhQc,discussion-id=E6BeJEiw,comment-id=000c,timestamp=2018-12-02T07:26:12.750+0000)
>
> Yup.  No surprise, though.  
> Riot - &quot;We&#x27;re going to ruin the forums and create reddit like boards instead.&quot;
> Nearly everyone that used the forums &quot;Please, don&#x27;t do that.  You have reddit for that?  Can we please keep our forum?&quot;
> Riot - &quot;No.  We need to do this so that we have better communication with you guys.  Whether you like it or not, it will be better in the long run.&quot;
> Community - &quot;Well... we still don&#x27;t like it, but if you insist.&quot;
> Riot - *creates boards*
> Community - *realizes they&#x27;re garbage and creates a post with thousands of upvotes (that is seemingly gone now) saying boards are garbage*
> Riot - &quot;Damn.  They were right.  These boards are trash.  Oh well.  Let&#x27;s just go talk shit about them on twitter.&quot; Lol.

Don't worry, the boards are still in beta. They'll make it better by the full release!

*5 years later, boards still in "beta," and Riot hasn't really updated it since the boards were initially released*

...Yeah, I got nothin'
